Deputy National Security Advisor Ben Rhodes met with members of the Iraqi Yezidi community to discuss the dire humanitarian situation in northern Iraq. They discussed the suffering of the Yezidi community and other minority groups at the hands of ISIL, including starvation, kidnappings, and executions. Rhodes mentioned President Obama's decision to conduct humanitarian airdrops and authorize targeted airstrikes to help those trapped on Mount Sinjar. He condemned ISIL's atrocities and emphasized that the US will act responsibly to prevent potential genocide. Rhodes also highlighted the importance of empowering Iraqis to confront the crisis and form an inclusive government. He expressed admiration for the resilience of the Yezidi community and stated that the US will continue to provide humanitarian support and work towards a lasting solution.